The paper deals with algorithms for compiling connected crossing-free geometric graphs into directed acyclic graphs (DAGs) and optimizing them. This involves techniques for dealing with connectivity constraints, spanning trees, and spanning cycles. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CG (Computational Geometry), which deals with algorithms and data structures for geometric problems. 

The paper also involves counting, enumeration, and random sampling, which are topics covered in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). 

Optimization is a topic covered in cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). 

Finally, the paper involves the use of DAGs, which are a topic covered in cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
